This paper discusses approximate query processing, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the limitations and challenges of sample-based joins, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the context of AQP.
